ecisions based on comparable and transparent data.\n\n### Open source\n\nThe database is open to build upon, under CC BY SA 4.0 license.\n\n### Database\n\nAn open, democratized, global, free, comparable, transparent, actionable, open\nsource database.\n\n## Report\n\nDo you see some missing data? Please help fill the gaps. You are more than\nwelcome to contribute to build a free, open, global, sustainability data\nplatform. Your actions matter.\n\nReport Data\n\n## Support\n\nWe invite you to be part of this open sustainability data platform.\n\nWhether you are an individual seeking to make a difference, a company aiming\nto disclose your commitment to a sustainable society, or a researcher in\npursuit of the truth, our doors are open.\n\nWe need your support. We\u2019re a non-profit organization, dedicated to making the\nworld\u2019s sustainability available, accessible, open and free for all. We need\nyour support to make that happen.\n\nRead more\n\n## By the numbers\n\nOur mission is to encompass all publicly reported sustainability data. At the\noutset, we\u2019re currently covering 530 major corporations across 58 industries,\nrepresenting a total revenue of 62.374 billion USD. We aspire to expand this\nscope significantly, leveraging the support of a global community.\n\n## 530\n\nCompanies\n\n## 58\n\nIndustries\n\n## 62,374B\n\n$USD Revenue\n\n## 24,684B\n\nton CO2e emissions reported\n\n###### Open Sustainability Index\n\nCompanies\n\nIndustries\n\nDocumentation\n\nAbout\n\nNews\n\nSupport Us\n\nContact\n\nAPI\n\nRoadmap\n\nLicensed under CC BY-SA 4.0\n\n  * Companies\n\n  * Industries\n\n  * Documentation\n\n  * About\n\n  * API\n\nReport Data\n\n", "frontpage": false}
